T1  - A Role and Expectancy Perception Model of Participation in Decision Making
AU  - Schuler, Randall S.
Y1  - 1980/06/01
PY  - 1980
DA  - 1980/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255435
DO  - 10.5465/255435
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 331
EP  - 340
VL  - 23
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Based on some suggestions in the literature, a model was developed to illustrate the ?how? of participation in decision making. The model depicts role and expectancy perceptions in explaining how participation mediates the relationship between participation in decision making and employee attitudes. It therefore may offer a parsimonious framework in which to explain the influence of several organizational and individual conditions on the participation process.
AB  - Based on some suggestions in the literature, a model was developed to illustrate the ?how? of participation in decision making. The model depicts role and expectancy perceptions in explaining how participation mediates the relationship between participation in decision making and employee attitudes. It therefore may offer a parsimonious framework in which to explain the influence of several organizational and individual conditions on the participation process.
