T1  - WOMEN AS MANAGERS: ATTITUDES AND ATTRIBUTIONS FOR PERFORMANCE BY MEN AND WOMEN
AU  - Stevens, George E.
AU  - Denisi, Angelo S.
Y1  - 1980/06/01
PY  - 1980
DA  - 1980/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255438
DO  - 10.5465/255438
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 355
EP  - 361
VL  - 23
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article presents a replication of a study that investigated the relationships between attitudes towards women as managers. The study examines a number of attributions for the success and failure of women managers. Also discussed are a number of problems encountered by women who are attempting to gain access to male occupations. The article presents the influence of descriptions of success or failure of women managers to popular attitudes toward women as managers. The study is based on the assumption that these attitudes are stable and not situation specific.
AB  - The article presents a replication of a study that investigated the relationships between attitudes towards women as managers. The study examines a number of attributions for the success and failure of women managers. Also discussed are a number of problems encountered by women who are attempting to gain access to male occupations. The article presents the influence of descriptions of success or failure of women managers to popular attitudes toward women as managers. The study is based on the assumption that these attitudes are stable and not situation specific.
