T1  - Job Switching in Autonomous Work Groups: An Exploratory Study in a Pennsylvania Coal Mine
AU  - Blumberg, Melvin
Y1  - 1980/06/01
PY  - 1980
DA  - 1980/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255432
DO  - 10.5465/255432
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 287
EP  - 306
VL  - 23
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This 13-month field study explores the phenomenon of job-switching behavior and attempts to isolate some of the critical variables associated with job switching in autonomous work groups. Results indicate that age and job status are strong influences on job switching. Job switching correlated negatively with job satisfaction and positively with absenteeism, feedback, task identity, and hazard.
AB  - This 13-month field study explores the phenomenon of job-switching behavior and attempts to isolate some of the critical variables associated with job switching in autonomous work groups. Results indicate that age and job status are strong influences on job switching. Job switching correlated negatively with job satisfaction and positively with absenteeism, feedback, task identity, and hazard.
